ctually very I mean, he''s getting closer and closer to to to this PIS guy. And, actually, this is kind of the, do do do you call it, white horse? Is it Black horse. No. Black horse. That that horse. Right? Of elections. So he he may change a lot in the election because because, you know, if if the the the the support for for democratic, candidate is strong, but it is not sufficient to win in the first turn, first round. And, there will be second round, and, it it is it is almost hundred percent sure that in second round, he''s winning with, with PIS guy, but and very significantly. However, if in second round, there will be this guy, the conservative guy, it is not as clear whether, you know, who will be winning. Even even he''s he has much less at the moment in the in the in the first round than the PIS guy. So this might be, you know, this might be interesting, but the the bad bad thing is that, if this, if this, conservative guy win, it will be bad news for Paul. It will be I mean, actually, everyone who everyone else than the democratic candidate, is a very bad news for Paul.", "confidence": 0.9885254, "words": [{"word": "very", "start": 0.24, "end": 0.48, "confidence": 0.50439453, "punctuated_word": "Very"}, {"word": "interesting", "start": 0.48, "end": 0.98, "confidence": 0.6328125, "punctuated_word": "interesting"}, {"word": "political", "start": 1.12, "end": 1.5999999, "confidence": 1, "punctuated_word": "political"}, {"word": "situation", "start": 1.5999999, "end": 2.1, "confidence": 1, "punctuated_word": "situation"}, {"word": "because", "start": 2.1599998, "end": 2.6599998, "confidence": 0.86328125, "punctuated_word": "because"}, {"word": "they", "start": 3.28, "end": 3.4399998, "confidence": 0.4375, "punctuated_word": "they"}, {"word": "as", "start": 3.6, "end": 4, "confidence": 0.9970703, "punctuated_word": "as"}, {"word": "always", "start": 4, "end": 4.5, "confidence": 0.99609375, "punctuated_word": "always,"}, {"word": "we", "start": 4.64, "end": 4.8